alue: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31254\" xsd:anyURI\n5839:is_obsolete: true\n5840-\n5841-[Term]\n--\n5847-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/22916\" xsd:anyURI\n5848:is_obsolete: true\n5849-\n5850-[Term]\n--\n5885-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/22916\" xsd:anyURI\n5886:is_obsolete: true\n5887-\n5888-[Term]\n--\n6322-def: \"OBSOLETE. Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving amino acids of the glutamine family, comprising arginine, glutamate, glutamine and proline.\" [GOC:curators]\n6323:comment: The reason for obsoletion is that this is an unnecessary grouping term.\n6324-synonym: \"regulation of glutamine family amino acid metabolism\" EXACT []\n6325-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/29444\" xsd:anyURI\n6326:is_obsolete: true\n6327-\n6328-[Term]\n--\n6335-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30570\" xsd:anyURI\n6336:is_obsolete: true\n6337-\n6338-[Term]\n--\n6403-synonym: \"inositol pyrophosphate synthase activity\" EXACT []\n6404:is_obsolete: true\n6405-\n6406-[Term]\n--\n6567-def: \"OBSOLETE. Any process that modulates the surface configuration of a cell during the vegetative growth phase. The vegetative growth phase is the growth phase during which single celled organisms reproduce by budding or other asexual methods.\" [GOC:clt, GOC:curators, GOC:vw]\n6568:comment: The reason for obsoletion is that biological phases should be captured as extensions.\n6569-synonym: \"cell morphogenesis during vegetative growth phase\" RELATED [GOC:vw]\n6570-synonym: \"cellular morphogenesis during vegetative growth\" RELATED [GOC:dph, GOC:tb]\n6571-synonym: \"regulation of cell morphogenesis during vegetative growth phase\" RELATED []\n6572:is_obsolete: true\n6573-\