19-\n--\n53227-synonym: \"high-density lipoprotein\" EXACT []\n53228:is_obsolete: true\n53229-replaced_by: GO:0005319\n53230-\n--\n53238-synonym: \"low-density lipoprotein\" EXACT []\n53239:is_obsolete: true\n53240-replaced_by: GO:0005319\n53241-\n--\n53249-synonym: \"VLDL\" EXACT []\n53250:is_obsolete: true\n53251-replaced_by: GO:0005319\n53252-\n--\n53411-def: \"OBSOLETE. Enables the transfer of organic acids from one side of a membrane to the other. Organic acids are acidic compound containing carbon in covalent linkage.\" [ISBN:0198506732]\n53412:comment: The reason for obsoletion is that this term was an unnecessary and confusing grouping term.\n53413-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30715\" xsd:anyURI\n53414:is_obsolete: true\n53415-replaced_by: GO:0022857\n53416-\n--\n53556-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/27326\" xsd:anyURI\n53557:is_obsolete: true\n53558-replaced_by: GO:0055056\n53559-\n--\n53581-def: \"OBSOLETE. Enables the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction: glucose + H+ = glucose + H+. This activity is constitutive and therefore always present, regardless of demand. Symporter activity enables the active transport of a solute across a membrane by a mechanism whereby two or more species are transported together in the same direction in a tightly coupled process not directly linked to a form of energy other than chemiosmotic energy.\" [GOC:mtg_transport]\n53582:comment: The reason for obsoletion is that the constitutive aspect of the transporter is unlikely to be an aspect of the activity, but instead it probably relates to the expression level of the transporter.\n53583-synonym: \"constitutive hydrogen/glucose transporter activity\" BROAD []\n53584-synonym: \"constitutive hydrogen:glucose symporter activity\" EXACT []\n53585-synonym: \"constitutive hydrogen:glucose transporter activity\" BROAD []\n53586:is_obsolete: true\n53587-\n53588-[Term]\n--\n53734-synonym: \"metal ion transporter\" BROAD []\n53735:is_obsolete: true\n53736-consider: GO:0015291\n53737-consider: GO:0046873\n--\n53762-synonym: \"plasma membrane copper transporter\" EXACT []\n53763:is_obsolete: true\n53764-consider: GO:0005375\n53765-consider: GO:0005886\n--\n53774-synonym: \"intracellular copper transporter\" EXACT []\n53775:is_obsolete: true\n53776-consider: GO:0005375\n53777-consider: GO:0005622\n--\n53888-comment: This term has been obsoleted because eye pigment precursors are nucleotides and amino acids, and there are terms to annotate these functions.\n53889:is_obsolete: true\n53890-\n53891-[Term]\n--\n53897-synonym: \"transmembrane conductance regulator activity\" EXACT []\n53898:is_obsolete: true\n53899-consider: GO:0043267\n53900-\n--\n53907-synonym: \"peroxisomal membrane transporter\" EXACT []\n53908:is_obsolete: true\n53909-consider: GO:0005215\n53910-consider: GO:0005777\n--\n53980-comment: The term was obsoleted because its intended usage was unclear: chromaffin granules are dense core secretory vesicles (PMID:20853344) so whatever they transport must be by secretion.\n53981:is_obsolete: true\n53982-\n53983-[Term]\n--\n53988-comment: The class was obsoleted because the cellular location of a function should not be part of the class label.\n53989:is_obsolete: true\n53990-consider: GO:0005275\n53991-\n--\n54036-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/24479\" xsd:anyURI\n54037:is_obsolete: true\n54038-\n54039-[Term]\n--\n54142-synonym: \"small-molecule carrier or transporter\" EXACT []\n54143:is_obsolete: true\n54144-consider: GO:0005215\n54145-\n--\n54203-synonym: \"vacuolar assembly\" EXACT []\n54204:is_obsolete: true\n54205-replaced_by: GO:0007033\n54206-\n--\n54213-synonym: \"vesicle transport\" EXACT []\n54214:is_obsolete: true\n54215-replaced_by: GO:0016192\n54216-\n--\n54223-synonym: \"vesicle fusion\" EXACT []\n5422