er: GO:0000794\n--\n56336-synonym: \"meiotic chromosome\" EXACT []\n56337:is_obsolete: true\n56338-consider: GO:0000794\n56339-\n--\n56416-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/19086\" xsd:anyURI\n56417:is_obsolete: true\n56418-\n56419-[Term]\n--\n56511-synonym: \"snoRNA\" EXACT []\n56512:is_obsolete: true\n56513-\n56514-[Term]\n--\n56520-synonym: \"box C + D snoRNP protein\" EXACT []\n56521:is_obsolete: true\n56522-\n56523-[Term]\n--\n56529-synonym: \"box H + ACA snoRNP protein\" EXACT []\n56530:is_obsolete: true\n56531-\n56532-[Term]\n--\n56664-def: \"OBSOLETE. The protein complexes that form the mitochondrial electron transport system (the respiratory chain), associated with the inner mitochondrial membrane. The respiratory chain complexes transfer electrons from an electron donor to an electron acceptor and are associated with a proton pump to create a transmembrane electrochemical gradient.\" [GOC:curators, GOC:ecd, ISBN:0198547684]\n56665:comment: The reason for obsoletion is that this term unnecssarily specified a cellular compartment.\n56666-synonym: \"mitochondrial electron transport chain\" EXACT []\n56667-synonym: \"mitochondrial respiratory chain\" EXACT []\n--\n56671-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/27253\" xsd:anyURI\n56672:is_obsolete: true\n56673-replaced_by: GO:0098803\n56674-created_by: pr\n--\n56682-def: \"OBSOLETE. A protein complex located in the mitochondrial inner membrane that forms part of the mitochondrial respiratory chain. It contains about 25 different polypeptide subunits, including NADH dehydrogenase (ubiquinone), flavin mononucleotide and several different iron-sulfur clusters containing non-heme iron. The iron undergoes oxidation-reduction between Fe(II) and Fe(III), and catalyzes proton translocation linked to the oxidation of NADH by ubiquinone.\" [GOC:mtg_sensu, ISBN:0198547684]\n56683:comment: The reason for obsoletion is that this term unnecssarily specified a cellular compartment.\n56684-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/27253\" xsd:anyURI\n56685:is_obsolete: true\n56686-replaced_by: GO:0045271\n56687-\n--\n56696-def: \"OBSOLETE. A protein complex located in the mitochondrial inner membrane that forms part of the mitochondrial respiratory chain. Contains the four polypeptide subunits of succinate dehydrogenase, flavin-adenine dinucleotide and iron-sulfur. Catalyzes the oxidation of succinate by ubiquinone. Connects the TCA cycle with the respiratory chain.\" [GOC:mtg_sensu, GOC:vw, ISBN:0198547684]\n56697:comment: The reason for obsoletion is that this term unnecssarily specified a cellular compartment.\n56698-synonym: \"mitochondrial fumarate reductase complex\" EXACT []\n56699-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/27253\" xsd:anyURI\n56700:is_obsolete: true\n56701-replaced_by: GO:0045273\n56702-\n--\n56708-def: \"OBSOLETE. A protein complex located in the mitochondrial inner membrane that forms part of the mitochondrial respiratory chain. Contains about 10 polypeptide subunits including four redox centers: cytochrome b/b6, cytochrome c1 and an 2Fe-2S cluster. Catalyzes the oxidation of ubiquinol by oxidized cytochrome c1.\" [GOC:mtg_sensu, ISBN:0198547684]\n56709:comment: The reason for obsoletion is that this term unnecssarily specified a cellular compartment.\n56710-synonym: \"mitochondrial coenzyme Q-cytochrome c oxidoreductase complex\" EXACT []\n56711-synonym: \"mitochondrial coenzyme Q-cytochrome c reductase complex\" EXACT []\n--\n56718-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/27253\" xsd:anyURI\n56719:is_obsolete: true\n56720-replaced_by: GO:0045275\n56721-\n--\n56727-def: \"OBSOLETE. A protein complex located in the mitochondrial inner membrane that forms part of the mitochondrial respiratory chain. Contains the 13 polypeptide subunits of cytochrome c oxidase, including cytochrome a and cytochrome a3. Catalyzes the oxidation of reduced cytochrome c by dioxygen (O2).\" [GOC:mtg_sensu, ISBN:0198547684]\n56728:comment: The reason for obsoletion is that this term unnecssarily specified a cellular compartment.\n56729-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/27253\" xsd:anyURI\n56730:is_obsolete: true\n56731-replaced_by: GO:0045277\n56732-\n--\n56738-def: \"OBSOLETE. A proton-transporting ATP synthase complex found in the mitochondrial membrane.\" [GOC:mah, GOC:mtg_sensu]\n56739:comment: The reason for obsoletion is that this term unnecssarily specified a cellular compartment.\n56740-synonym: \"mitochondrial respiratory chain complex V\" EXACT []\n56741-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/27253\" xsd:anyURI\n56742:is_obsolete: true\n56743-replaced_by: GO:0045259\n56744-\n--\n56749-def: \"OBSOLETE. The hexamer, comprising three alpha and three beta subunits, that possesses the catalytic activity of the mitochondrial hydrogen-transporting ATP synthase.\" [GOC:mtg_sensu, PMID:10838056]\n56750:comment: The reason for obsoletion is that this term unnecssarily specified a cellular compartment.\n56751-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/27253\" xsd:anyURI\n56752:is_obsolete: true\n56753-replaced_by: GO:0045259\n56754-\n--\n56761-synonym: \"hydrogen-transporting ATP synthase, coupling factor CF(0)\" EXACT []\n56762:is_obsolete: true\n56763-consider: GO:0045259\n56764-\n--\n56769-def: \"OBSOLETE. One of two stalks that connect the catalytic core of the hydrogen-transporting ATP synthase to the mitochondrial membrane-associated F0 proteins; rotates within the catalytic core during catalysis.\" [GOC:mtg_sensu, PMID:10838056]\n56770:comment: The reason for obsoletion is that this term unnecssarily specified a cellular compartment.\n56771-property_value: term_tracke