nting a linear array of ribosomes held together by messenger RNA. They represent the active complexes in cellular protein synthesis and are able to incorporate amino acids into polypeptides both in vivo and in vitro.\" [ISBN:0198506732, NIF_Subcellular:sao1038025871]\n57730:comment: The reason for obsoletion is that the term is out of scope for GO.\n57731-synonym: \"polyribosome\" EXACT [NIF_Subcellular:sao1038025871]\n57732-xref: NIF_Subcellular:sao1038025871\n--\n57734-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/24651\" xsd:anyURI\n57735:is_obsolete: true\n57736-consider: GO:0005840\n57737-\n--\n57742-def: \"OBSOLETE. Any protein complex that binds to an mRNA cap at any time in the lifetime of the mRNA.\" [GOC:jid]\n57743:comment: The reason for obsoletion is that this term was an unnecessary grouping term.\n57744-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/26347\" xsd:anyURI\n57745:is_obsolete: true\n57746-\n57747-[Term]\n--\n57949-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31956\" xsd:anyURI\n57950:is_obsolete: true\n57951-replaced_by: GO:0008290\n57952-\n--\n58125-synonym: \"proteoglycan integral to plasma membrane\" EXACT []\n58126:is_obsolete: true\n58127-replaced_by: GO:0005886\n58128-\n--\n58321-synonym: \"clathrin adaptor\" EXACT []\n58322:is_obsolete: true\n58323-replaced_by: GO:0030119\n58324-\n--\n58332-synonym: \"HA1 clathrin adaptor\" EXACT []\n58333:is_obsolete: true\n58334-consider: GO:0030121\n58335-\n--\n58343-synonym: \"HA2 clathrin adaptor\" EXACT []\n58344:is_obsolete: true\n58345-consider: GO:0030122\n58346-\n--\n58478-def: \"OBSOLETE. An adherens junction which connects a cell to the extracellular matrix.\" [GOC:hb]\n58479:comment: The reason for obsoletion is that, based on the most recent literature, there is no such structure in biology as 'cell-substrate adherens junction'. An 'adherens junction' is always a 'cell-cell junction' (PMIDs: 20571587, 17854762, 21422226, 28096264, 28401269, 26923917).\n58480-synonym: \"hemi-adherens junction\" RELATED []\n58481:is_obsolete: true\n58482-\n58483-[Term]\n--\n58510-def: \"OBSOLETE. A cell-substrate adherens junction found in the apical region of a cell, such as those found in cuticle-secreting epithelia, which connect the apical membrane to the cuticle.\" [GOC:mah, PMID:11700298]\n58511:comment: The reason for obsoletion is that this term has not been used for GO annotation at all since 2001 when it was created, it has no children, it is not a part of any subset/slim.\n58512-synonym: \"apical cell-substrate adherens junction\" EXACT [GOC:mah]\n58513-synonym: \"apical dense plaque\" EXACT []\n58514:is_obsolete: true\n58515-\n58516-[Term]\n--\n58601-synonym: \"shmoo\" EXACT []\n58602:is_obsolete: true\n58603-consider: GO:0001400\n58604-consider: GO:0005937\n--\n58648-synonym: \"unlocalized protein complex\" EXACT []\n58649:is_obsolete: true\n58650-\n58651-[Term]\n--\n58720-def: \"OBSOLETE. Mitochondrial complex that possesses alpha-ketoglutarate dehydrogenase activity.\" [GOC:mah, GOC:mtg_sensu]\n58721:comment: The reason for obsoletion is that this term is equivalent to mitochondrial oxoglutarate dehydrogenase complex.\n58722-synonym: \"2-oxoglutarate dehydrogenase complex\" BROAD []\n58723-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/26122\" xsd:anyURI\n58724:is_obsolete: true\n58725-replaced_by: GO:0045252\n58726-\n--\n58744-synonym: \"aminoadipate-semialdehyde dehydrogenase complex\" EXACT []\n58745:is_obsolete: true\n58746-\n58747-[Term]\n--\n58831-synonym: \"debranching enzyme\" EXACT []\n58832:is_obsolete: true\n58833-consider: GO:0043033\n58834-\n--\n58869-def: \"OBSOLETE. Mitochondrial complex that possesses isocitrate dehydrogenase (NAD+) activity.\" [GOC:mah, GOC:mtg_sensu]\n58870:comment: The reason for obsoletion is that this term is unnecessarily taxon-specific.\n58871-property