olete: true\n72914-consider: GO:0007260\n72915-consider: GO:0046983\n--\n72921-def: \"OBSOLETE. An intracellular signaling cassette that starts with production of nitric oxide, detection by receptors/sensors for nitric oxide (such as soluble guanylyl cyclase/sGC) and ends with the activation of downstream effectors that further transmit the signal within the cell. Nitric oxide transmits its downstream effects through either cyclic GMP (cGMP)-dependent or independent mechanisms.\" [GOC:jl, PMID:21549190]\n72922:comment: The reason for obsoletion is that this term has been inconsistently used and NO signaling proceeds via cGMP, so the more specific replacement term is preferred.\n72923-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/26613\" xsd:anyURI\n72924:is_obsolete: true\n72925-replaced_by: GO:0038060\n72926-\n--\n73034-synonym: \"regulation of synapse\" EXACT []\n73035:is_obsolete: true\n73036-consider: GO:0007268\n73037-\n--\n73110-def: \"OBSOLETE. The directed movement of a pole cell (germline progenitors in insects) from its site of production at the posterior pole of the embryo through to the site where the gonads will form.\" [GOC:bf, PMID:9988212]\n73111:comment: The reason for obsoletion is that the term is unnecessarily taxon-specific.\n73112-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/25689\" xsd:anyURI\n73113:is_obsolete: true\n73114-replaced_by: GO:0008354\n73115-\n--\n73352-def: \"OBSOLETE. The directed movement of cytoplasmic constituents synthesized in the nurse cells to the oocyte.\" [ISBN:0879694238]\n73353:comment: The reason for obsoletion is that this term was an unnecessary grouping term.\n73354-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/26386\" xsd:anyURI\n73355:is_obsolete: true\n73356-\n73357-[Term]\n--\n73611-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/12739\" xsd:anyURI\n