d not a real GO process.\n107176-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/21719\" xsd:anyURI\n107177:is_obsolete: true\n107178-\n107179-[Term]\n--\n107183-def: \"OBSOLETE. Any process that modulates the volume of a multivesicular body as part of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of a protein or peptide covalently tagged with ubiquitin.\" [GOC:dph, GOC:tb]\n107184:comment: The reason for obsoletion is that this term represents an assay and not a real GO process.\n107185-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/21719\" xsd:anyURI\n107186:is_obsolete: true\n107187-\n107188-[Term]\n--\n107372-def: \"OBSOLETE. Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of a process involved in the formation, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a mitochondrion.\" [GOC:dph, GOC:tb]\n107373:comment: The reason for obsoletion is that the meaning of the term is ambiguous.\n107374-synonym: \"positive regulation of mitochondrion organisation\" EXACT [GOC:mah]\n107375-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/26782\" xsd:anyURI\n107376:is_obsolete: true\n107377-\n107378-[Term]\n--\n107384-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/26782\" xsd:anyURI\n107385:is_obsolete: true\n107386-\n107387-[Term]\n--\n107480-synonym: \"telomere maintenance via telomere shortening\" EXACT []\n107481:is_obsolete: true\n107482-consider: GO:1903824\n107483-\n--\n107572-synonym: \"promoter binding\" EXACT []\n107573:is_obsolete: true\n107574-consider: GO:0000976\n107575-consider: GO:0001046\n--\n107608-comment: This term was obsoleted because 'chromatin assembly' was merged into 'chromatin organization'.\n107609:is_obsolete: true\n107610-replaced_by: GO:0006325\n107611-\n--\n107618-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/22847\" xsd:anyURI\n107619:is_obsolete: true\n107620-\n107621-[Term]\n--\n107629-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/22455\" xsd:anyURI\n107630:is_obsolete: true\n107631-\n107632-[Term]\n--\n107695-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/25457\" xsd:anyURI\n107696:is_obsolete: true\n107697-consider: GO:0004683\n107698-consider: GO:0004699\n--\n107721-synonym: \"proteasome regulator activity\" EXACT []\n107722:is_obsolete: true\n107723-consider: GO:0061135\n107724-consider: GO:0061136\n--\n107732-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/25531\" xsd:anyURI\n107733:is_obsolete: true\n107734-consider: GO:0030295\n107735-consider: GO:0060391\n--\n107741-def: \"OBSOLETE. Any process that increases the rate of phospholipase C activity.\" [GOC:dph, GOC:tb]\n107742:comment: The reason for obsoletion is that this term represents a molecular function.\n107743-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/27854\" xsd:anyURI\n107744:is_obsolete: true\n107745-\n107746-[Term]\n--\n107752-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/28482\" xsd:anyURI\n107753:is_obsolete: true\n107754-\n107755-[Term]\n--\n107796-def: \"OBSOLETE. Any process that modulates the frequency or rate of receptor biosynthesis. Receptor biosynthesis is the collection of chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of a receptor molecule, a macromolecule that undergoes combination with a hormone, neurotransmitter, drug or intracellular messenger to initiate a change in cell function.\" [GOC:BHF, GOC:tb]\n107797:comment: The reason for obsoletion is that those represent specific gene products, and genes annotated to those terms should be annotated to 'regulation of gene expression' or 'regulation of transcription' or some signaling term.\n107798-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/19900\" xsd:anyURI\n107799:is_obsolete: true\n107800-\n107801-[Term]\n--\n107805-def: \"OBSOLETE. Any process that increases the frequency or rate of receptor biosynthesis. Receptor biosynthesis is the collection of chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of a receptor molecule, a macromolecule that undergoes combination with a hormone, neurotransmitter, drug or intracellular messenger to initiate a change in cell function.\" [GOC:BHF, GOC:tb]\n107806:comment: The reason for obsoletion is that those represent specific gene products, and genes annotated to those terms should be annotated to 'regulation of gene expression' or 'regulation of transcription' or some signaling term.\n107807-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/19900\" xsd:anyURI\n107808:is_obsolete: true\n107809-\n107810-[Term]\n--\n107814-def: \"OBSOLETE. Any process that decreases the frequency or rate of receptor biosynthesis. Receptor biosynthesis is the collection of chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of a receptor molecule, a macromolecule that undergoes combination with a hormone, neurotransmitter, drug or intracellular messenger to initiate a change in cell function.\" [GOC:BHF, GOC:tb]\n107815:comment: The reason for obsoletion is that those represent specific gene products, and genes annotated to those terms should be annotated to 'regulation of gene expression' or 'regulation of transcription' or some signaling term.\n107816-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/19900\" xsd:anyURI\n107817:is_obsolete: true\n107818-\n107819-[Term]\n--\n107825-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/19255\" xsd:anyURI\n107826:is_obsolete: true\n107827-consider: GO:0008203\n107828-\n--\n107835-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/19255\" xsd:anyURI\n107836:is_obsolete: true\n107837-consider: GO:0008203\n107838-\n--\n108124-def: \"OBSOLETE. Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of UDP-glucose catabolism. UDP-glucose catabolic processes are the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of UDP-glucose, uridinediphosphoglucose, a substance composed of glucose in glycosidic linkage with uridine diphosphate.\" [GOC:BHF, GOC:tb]\n108125:comment: The reason for obsoletion is that this term is not clearly defined.\n108126-synonym: \"regulation of UDP-glucose catabolism\" EXACT [GOC:tb]\n108127-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30685\" xsd:anyURI\n108128:is_obsolete: true\n108129-\n108130-[Term]\n--\n108134-def: \"OBSOLETE. Any process that decreases the rate, frequency or extent of UDP-glucose catabolism. UDP-glucose catabolic processes are the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of UDP-glucose, uridinediphosphoglucose, a substance composed of glucose in glycosidic linkage with uridine diphosphate.\" [GOC:BHF, GOC:tb]\n108135:comment: The reason for obsoletion is that this term is not clearly defined.\n108136-synonym: \"negative regulation of UDP-glucose catabolism\" EXACT [GOC:tb]\n108137-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30685\" xsd:anyURI\n108138:is_obsolete: true\n108139-\n108140-[Term]\n--\n108185-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/28482\" xsd:anyURI\n108186:is_obsolete: true\n108187-\n108188-[Term]\n--\n108194-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/22455\" xsd:anyURI\n108195:is_obsolete: true\n108196-\n108197-[Term]\n--\n108203-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/22455\" xsd:anyURI\n108204:is_obsolete: true\n108205-\n108206-[Term]\n--\n108319-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/22455\" xsd:anyURI\n108320:is_obsolete: true\n108321-\n108322-[Term]\n--\n108328-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/22455\" xsd:anyURI\n108329:is_obsolete: true\n108330-\n108331-[Term]\n--\n108335-def: \"OBSOLETE. The process pertaining to the initial formation of an anatomical structure from unspecified parts. This process begins with the specific processes that contribute to the appearance of the discrete structure and ends when the structure is recognizable. An anatomical structure is any biological entity that occupies space and is distinguished from its surroundings. Anatomical structures can be macroscopic such as a carpel, or microscopic such as an acrosome.\" [GOC:dph, GOC:tb]\n108336:comment: The reason for obsoletion is that the term is confusing - it sounds developmental and has a developmental sounding def, but it is not a child of developmental process and its children included 'cellular component assembly'. The term was created to group together 'cellular component assembly' and 'anatomical structure formation involved in morphogenesis', but we no longer feel that this grouping is useful.\n108337-synonym: \"anatomical structure formation\" EXACT []\n108338:is_obsolete: true\n108339-consider: GO:0022607\n108340-consider: GO:0048646\n--\n108455-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/25218\" xsd:anyURI\n108456:is_obsolete: true\n108457-\n108458-[Term]\n--\n108464-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/25218\" xsd:anyURI\n108465:is_obsolete: true\n108466-\n108467-[Term]\n--\n108471-def: \"OBSOLETE. Any process that modulates the rate or frequency of cell death. Cell death is the specific activation or halting of processes within a cell so that its vital functions markedly cease, rather than simply deteriorating gradually over time, which culminates in cell death.\" [GO