ology/go-ontology/issues/29294\" xsd:anyURI\n111665:is_obsolete: true\n111666-replaced_by: GO:0015012\n111667-\n--\n111713-synonym: \"glypican\" EXACT []\n111714:is_obsolete: true\n111715-\n111716-[Term]\n--\n111902-synonym: \"syndecan\" EXACT []\n111903:is_obsolete: true\n111904-\n111905-[Term]\n--\n111925-synonym: \"GPI-anchored membrane-bound receptor\" EXACT []\n111926:is_obsolete: true\n111927-\n111928-[Term]\n--\n111945-synonym: \"internalization receptor activity\" EXACT []\n111946:is_obsolete: true\n111947-\n111948-[Term]\n--\n111979-def: \"OBSOLETE. The incorporation of hemolymph proteins by cells of the fat body of holometabolous insects, during the final larval stage. Uptake of these proteins prepares the insect for pupation and metamorphosis, since insect pupae do not feed and therefore depend on material that has been accumulated during larval life.\" [GOC:bf, PMID:10231363]\n111980:comment: The reason for obsoletion is that the data from the paper for which the term was requested can be accurately described using 'receptor-mediated endocytosis'.\n111981-synonym: \"fat body metabolic process\" BROAD []\n111982-synonym: \"fat body metabolism\" BROAD []\n--\n111989-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/12935\" xsd:anyURI\n111990:is_obsolete: true\n111991-\n111992-[Term]\n--\n111998-synonym: \"cytochrome P450 activity\" EXACT []\n111999:is_obsolete: true\n112000-consider: GO:0019825\n112001-\n--\n112043-def: \"OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the reaction: oxidized adrenodoxin + NADPH + H+ = reduced adrenodoxin + NADP+.\" [GOC:kd]\n112044:comment: The reason for obsoletion is that this term is equivalent to ferredoxin-NADP+ reductase activity.\n112045-synonym: \"adrenodoxin reductase activity\" BROAD []\n112046-synonym: \"adrenodoxin-type ferredoxin reductase activity\" EXACT [GOC:kd]\n--\n112048-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/29598\" xsd:anyURI\n112049:is_obsole