16303\n112435-consider: GO:0035005\n--\n112444-synonym: \"phosphatidylinositol 3-kinase, class I, regulator activity\" EXACT []\n112445:is_obsolete: true\n112446-replaced_by: GO:0046935\n112447-\n--\n112474-synonym: \"heavy metal ion transporter activity\" EXACT []\n112475:is_obsolete: true\n112476-consider: GO:0046873\n112477-\n--\n112658-synonym: \"manganese resistance permease activity\" EXACT []\n112659:is_obsolete: true\n112660-\n112661-[Term]\n--\n112707-def: \"OBSOLETE. Enables the transfer of organic cations from one side of a membrane to the other. Organic cations are atoms or small molecules with a positive charge that contain carbon in covalent linkage.\" [GOC:ai, GOC:mtg_transport, ISBN:0815340729]\n112708:comment: The reason for obsoletion is that this term was an unnecessary and confusing grouping term.\n112709-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30715\" xsd:anyURI\n112710:is_obsolete: true\n112711-replaced_by: GO:0022857\n112712-\n--\n112717-def: \"OBSOLETE. Enables the transfer of inorganic anions from one side of a membrane to the other. Inorganic anions are atoms or small molecules with a negative charge which do not contain carbon in covalent linkage.\" [GOC:ai]\n112718:comment: The reason for obsoletion is that this term was an unnecessary and confusing grouping term.\n112719-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30715\" xsd:anyURI\n112720:is_obsolete: true\n112721-replaced_by: GO:0022857\n112722-\n--\n112838-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/27121\" xsd:anyURI\n112839:is_obsolete: true\n112840-replaced_by: GO:0005315\n112841-created_by: pr\n--\n113363-def: \"OBSOLETE. Enables the transfer of propanediol from one side of a membrane to the other. Propanediol is a sweet colorless, viscous, hygroscopic liquid used as an antifreeze and in brake fluid; it is also as a humectant in cosmetics and personal care items, although it can be absorbed through the skin with harmful effects.\" [GOC:ai]\n113364:comment: The reason for obsoletion is that there is no evidence that this function exists.\n113365-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30214\" xsd:anyURI\n113366:is_obsolete: true\n113367-\n113368-[Term]\n--\n113433-synonym: \"holin\" EXACT []\n113434:is_obsolete: true\n113435-consider: GO:0019835\n113436-\n--\n113822-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/17005\" xsd:anyURI\n113823:is_obsolete: true\n113824-\n113825-[Term]\n--\n113854-synonym: \"vitamin/cofactor transporter activity\" EXACT []\n113855:is_obsolete: true\n113856-consider: GO:0090482\n113857-\n--\n114003-def: \"OBSOLETE. Enables the transfer of amiloride from one side of a membrane to the other. Amiloride is a potent and specific inhibitor of sodium ion entry into cells. It is used as a potassium-sparing diuretic.\" [ISBN:0198506732]\n114004:comment: The reason for obsoletion is that these terms are beyond the scope of GO.\n114005-synonym: \"amiloride transporter activity\" RELATED []\n114006-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/21394\" xsd:anyURI\n114007:is_obsolete: true\n114008-\n114009-[Term]\n--\n114062-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/14793\" xsd:anyURI\n114063:is_obsolete: true\n114064-consider: GO:0030228\n114065-consider: GO:0034041\n--\n114101-synonym: \"sugar/polyol channel activity\" EXACT []\n114102:is_obsolete: true\n114103-consider: GO:0015166\n114104-consider: GO:0051119\n--\n114122-def: \"OBSOLETE. Enables the energy-independent facilitated diffusion of propanediol through a transmembrane aqueous pore or channel.\" [GOC:mtg_transport]\n114123:comment: The reason for obsoletion is that there is no evidence that this function exists.\n114124-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://git