2019-10-03T15:29:54Z\n--\n466039-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/24261\" xsd:anyURI\n466040:is_obsolete: true\n466041-consider: GO:0140851\n466042-created_by: pg\n--\n467047-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/22043\" xsd:anyURI\n467048:is_obsolete: true\n467049-created_by: pg\n467050-creation_date: 2020-05-06T07:46:53Z\n--\n467056-def: \"OBSOLETE. The organization of chromatin into heterochromatin at the pericentric region of a chromosome.\" [PMID:26744419]\n467057:comment: The reason for obsoletion is that the term is not clearly defined and usage has been inconsistent.\n467058-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/19396\" xsd:anyURI\n467059-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31331\" xsd:anyURI\n467060:is_obsolete: true\n467061-created_by: pg\n467062-creation_date: 2020-05-06T07:47:09Z\n--\n467743-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/26610\" xsd:anyURI\n467744:is_obsolete: true\n467745-replaced_by: GO:1900744\n467746-created_by: pg\n--\n467756-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/26610\" xsd:anyURI\n467757:is_obsolete: true\n467758-replaced_by: GO:1903753\n467759-created_by: pg\n--\n467801-def: \"OBSOLETE. A transcription corepressor activity that represses or decreases the transcription of specific gene sets via binding to a DNA-bound nuclear receptor, either on its own or as part of a complex. Nuclear receptor corepressors often act by altering chromatin structure and modifications. For example, one class of transcription nuclear receptor corepressors modifies chromatin structure through covalent modification of histones. A second class remodels the conformation of chromatin in an ATP-dependent fashion. A third class modulates interactions of DNA-bound DNA-binding transcription factors with other transcription coregulators.\" [PMID:7566114, PMID:7566126, PMID:9238851]\n467802:comment: The reason for obsoletion is that these activities are not necessarily specific for nuclear receptors subclass of dbTFs, so that distinction leads to misannotations.\n467803-synonym: \"nuclear corepressor activity\" BROAD []\n467804-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/20262\" xsd:anyURI\n--\n467806-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/29150\" xsd:anyURI\n467807:is_obsolete: true\n467808-replaced_by: GO:0003714\n467809-created_by: pg\n--\n467949-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/18979\" xsd:anyURI\n467950:is_obsolete: true\n467951-replaced_by: GO:0044478\n467952-created_by: pg\n--\n468185-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/20675\" xsd:anyURI\n468186:is_obsolete: true\n468187-consider: GO:0016722\n468188-created_by: pg\n--\n468449-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/20876\" xsd:anyURI\n468450:is_obsolete: true\n468451-replaced_by: GO:0016887\n468452-created_by: pg\n--\n468592-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/24494\" xsd:anyURI\n468593:is_obsolete: true\n468594-consider: GO:0040029\n468595-created_by: pg\n--\n469047-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/22542\" xsd:anyURI\n469048:is_obsolete: true\n469049-replaced_by: GO:1900772\n469050-created_by: pg\n--\n469075-property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/26545\" xsd:anyURI\n469076:is_obsolete: true\n469077-consider: GO:0007005\n469078-created_by: pg\n--\n470249-def: \"OBSOLETE. Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of transcription of a non-protein coding gene from a DNA-templat